{"name": "django-querysetsequence", "metadata": {"name": "django-querysetsequence", "version": "0.17", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Environment :: Web Environment", "Framework :: Django", "Framework :: Django :: 3.2", "Framework :: Django :: 4.0", "Framework :: Django :: 4.1", "Framework :: Django :: 4.2", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: ISC License (ISCL)", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Internet", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules"], "home_page": "https://github.com/clokep/django-querysetsequence", "license": "ISC", "documentation_url": "https://django-querysetsequence.readthedocs.io", "dependencies": ["django"], "summary": "Chain together multiple (disparate) QuerySets to treat them as a single QuerySet.", "upload_time": 1687887321}, "documentation": ["---\nsubstitutions:\n  QuerySets: '`QuerySets`'\n---\n\n# Django QuerySetSequence\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/django-querysetsequence.svg\n:target: https://pypi.org/project/django-querysetsequence/\n```\n\n```{image} https://github.com/clokep/django-querysetsequence/actions/workflows/main.yml/badge.svg\n:target: https://github.com/clokep/django-querysetsequence/actions/workflows/main.yml\n```\n\n```{image} https://readthedocs.org/projects/django-querysetsequence/badge/?version=latest\n:alt: Documentation Status\n:target: https://django-querysetsequence.readthedocs.io/en/latest/?badge=latest\n```\n\n% include-start\n\ndjango-querysetsequence adds helpers for treating multiple disparate `QuerySet`\nobejcts as a single `QuerySet`. This is useful for passing into APIs that only\naccepted a single `QuerySet`.\n\nThe `QuerySetSequence` wrapper is used to combine multiple `QuerySet` instances.\n\n## Overview\n\n`QuerySetSequence` aims to provide the same behavior as Django's [QuerySets],\nbut applied across multiple `QuerySet` instances.\n\nSupported features:\n\n- Methods that take a list of fields (e.g. `filter()`, `exclude()`,\n  `get()`, `order_by()`) must use fields that are common across all\n  sub-`QuerySets`.\n- Relationships across related models work (e.g. `'foo__bar'`, `'foo'`, or\n  `'foo_id'`). syntax).\n- The sub-`QuerySets` are evaluated as late as possible (e.g. during\n  iteration, slicing, pickling, `repr()`/`len()`/`list()`/`bool()`\n  calls).\n- Public `QuerySet` API methods that are untested/unimplemented raise\n  `NotImplementedError`.\n\n## Getting Started\n\nInstall the package using pip.\n\n```bash\npip install --upgrade django-querysetsequence\n```\n\n## Basic Usage\n\n```python\n# Import QuerySetSequence\nfrom queryset_sequence import QuerySetSequence\n\n# Create QuerySets you want to chain.\nfrom .models import SomeModel, OtherModel\n\n# Chain them together.\nquery = QuerySetSequence(SomeModel.objects.all(), OtherModel.objects.all())\n\n# Use query as if it were a QuerySet! E.g. in a ListView.\n```\n\n## Project Information\n\ndjango-querysetsequence is released under the ISC license, its documentation lives\non [Read the Docs], the code on [GitHub], and the latest release on [PyPI]. It\nsupports Python 3.7+, Django 3.2/4.0/4.1/4.2, and is optionally compatible with\n[Django REST Framework] 3.11+.\n\nSome ways that you can contribute:\n\n- Check for open issues or open a fresh issue to start a discussion around a\n  feature idea or a bug.\n- Fork the repository on GitHub to start making your changes.\n- Write a test which shows that the bug was fixed or that the feature works as\n  expected.\n- Send a pull request and bug the maintainer until it gets merged and published.\n\n[django rest framework]: http://www.django-rest-framework.org/\n[github]: https://github.com/clokep/django-querysetsequence\n[pypi]: https://pypi.org/project/django-querysetsequence/\n[querysets]: https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/ref/models/querysets/\n[read the docs]: https://django-querysetsequence.readthedocs.io/\n"], "modules": [{"name": "queryset_sequence.pagination", "documentation": ["More efficient pagination for django-querysetsequence when using Django REST\nFramework.\n\nThe standard Django REST Framework pagination classes will work fine. The\nclasses provided here are useful when providing large datasets that use\nQuerySetSequence over an API as they first order by the QuerySet number and then\nparticular fields."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "queryset_sequence.pagination.SequenceCursorPagination", "bases": ["CursorPagination"], "methods": [{"name": "queryset_sequence.pagination.SequenceCursorPagination.paginate_queryset", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "queryset", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "view", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "queryset_sequence.pagination.SequenceCursorPagination.get_ordering", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Take whatever the expected ordering is and then first order by QuerySet."]}, {"name": "queryset_sequence.pagination.SequenceCursorPagination._get_position_from_instance", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "instance", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ordering", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["The position will be a tuple of values:\n\n    The QuerySet number inside of the QuerySetSequence.\n    Whatever the normal value taken from the ordering property gives."]}, {"name": "queryset_sequence.pagination.SequenceCursorPagination.decode_cursor", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Given a request with a cursor, return a `Cursor` instance.\n\nDiffers from the standard CursorPagination to handle a tuple in the\nposition field."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Heavily customized CursorPagination to first sort by QuerySet, then by a\ndifferent ordering field.\n\nChanges include:\n* Don't override self.ordering with the output of get_ordering()\n* The filtering logic is significantly changed to deal with a tuple of fields."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "queryset_sequence", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "queryset_sequence.cmp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "a", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "b", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Compare two arbitrary values of the same type."]}, {"name": "queryset_sequence.multiply_iterables", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "it1", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "it2", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Element-wise iterables multiplications."]}, {"name": "queryset_sequence.cumsum", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "seq", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "queryset_sequence.BaseIterable", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "queryset_sequence.BaseIterable.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "querysetsequence", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "queryset_sequence.BaseIterable._get_fields", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*field_names", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Retrieve the values of fields from the object."]}, {"name": "queryset_sequence.BaseIterable._add_queryset_index", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Add the QuerySet index to the object and return the object."]}, {"name": "queryset_sequence.BaseIterable._get_field_names", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a list of field names that are part of a model."]}, {"name": "queryset_sequence.BaseIterable._cmp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value1", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value2", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Comparison method that takes into account Django's special rules when\nordering by a field that is a model:\n\n    1. Try following the default ordering on the related model.\n    2. Order by the model's primary key, if there is no Meta.ordering."]}, {"name": "queryset_sequence.BaseIterable._generate_comparator", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "field_names", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Construct a comparator function based on the field names. The comparator\nreturns the first non-zero comparison value.\n\nInputs:\n    field_names (iterable of strings): The field names to sort on.\n\nReturns:\n    A comparator function."]}, {"name": "queryset_sequence.BaseIterable._ordered_iterator", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Interleave the values of each QuerySet in order to handle the requested\nordering. Also adds the '#' property to each returned item."]},